
===================================
📌 1. Finglish Version (Persian Latin Script)
===================================

📖 **Tashrih:**
    Dastoor `busybox` mesle yek ja'be abzar ast ke tool-haye khoobi baraye kar ba system-haye Embeded va system-haye kuchak darad. Dar asl, chandin dastoor-e mohem-e Linux ra dar yek file-e ejraii ja dade ast.

⚙️ **Gozine-ha:**
    🔹 `busybox --list` --> 📜 List kardan hameye dastoorhaye dast-res
    🔹 `busybox [dastoor] --help` --> 👀 Raahnamaii baraye yek dastoor-e khass

🛠 **Mesal-ha:**

    $ busybox ls
    🔹 Namayesh file-ha dar poosheye fa'ali

    $ busybox df -h
    🔹 Didan fazaye disk be shekl ghabl-khani

✅ **Mesal sade:**

    $ busybox echo "Salam Donya!"
    🔹 Chap kardan "Salam Donya!" dar terminal. busybox echo mesle dastoor echo kar mikonad, amma az dakhele busybox ejra mishe.

===================================
📌 2. English Version
===================================

📖 **Description:**
    The `busybox` command is like a toolbox that contains many useful utilities for embedded and small systems.  It essentially bundles multiple essential Linux commands into a single executable.

⚙️ **Options:**
    🔹 `busybox --list` --> 📜 List all available commands.
    🔹 `busybox [command] --help` --> 👀 Get help for a specific command.

🛠 **Examples:**

    $ busybox ls
    🔹 List files in the current directory

    $ busybox df -h
    🔹 View disk space in human-readable format

✅ **Simple Example:**

    $ busybox echo "Hello World!"
    🔹 Prints "Hello World!" to the terminal. `busybox echo` works like the standard `echo` command, but executed through busybox.

